<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id464ac85b-3a70-11f1-a967-d35dac11796a" identifier="/us/usc/t26/s5706"><num value="5706">§ 5706.</num><heading> Drawback of tax</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">There shall be an allowance of drawback of tax paid on tobacco products and cigarette papers and tubes, when shipped from the United States, in accordance with such regulations and upon the filing of such bond as the Secretary shall prescribe.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="id464ac85c-3a70-11f1-a967-d35dac11796a">(<ref href="/us/act/1954-08-16/ch736">Aug. 16, 1954, ch. 736</ref>, <ref href="/us/stat/68A/709">68A Stat. 709</ref>; <ref href="/us/pl/85/859/tII/s202">Pub. L. 85–859, title II, § 202</ref>, <date date="1958-09-02">Sept. 2, 1958</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/72/1419">72 Stat. 1419</ref>; <ref href="/us/pl/94/455/tXIX/s1906/b/13/A">Pub. L. 94–455, title XIX, § 1906(b)(13)(A)</ref>, <date date="1976-10-04">Oct. 4, 1976</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/90/1834">90 Stat. 1834</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
<notes type="uscNote" id="id464ac85d-3a70-11f1-a967-d35dac11796a">
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" role="crossHeading" topic="editorialNotes" id="id464ac85e-3a70-11f1-a967-d35dac11796a"><heading class="centered"><b>Editorial Notes</b></heading></note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" topic="amendments" id="id464ac85f-3a70-11f1-a967-d35dac11796a"><heading class="centered smallCaps">Amendments</heading><p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">1976—<ref href="/us/pl/94/455">Pub. L. 94–455</ref> struck out “or his delegate” after “Secretary”.</p>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">1958—<ref href="/us/pl/85/859">Pub. L. 85–859</ref> substituted “tobacco products and cigarette papers and tubes” for “articles”.</p>
</note>
